      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The separation of strategy from execution is often maintained to prevent premature market speculation or internal dissent. Insisting on data accuracy, even amidst massive shifts, serves to ensure the foundations of the system remain sound, regardless of the underlying strategy. However, if the scope of the changes indicates systemic risk, that warrants a more serious approach than simple operational instructions. You might consider framing your concerns around operational risk rather than speculative market moves when discussing this with a more senior compliance or risk officer.",
